# User-defined brancher wrapper narrows types.
# `my-if(c, t, f): if(c, t, f)` is structurally equivalent to `if`.
# The BranchShape classifier must recognise it as a pass-through
# wrapper and apply the same If-shaped narrowing.
#
# `x` is annotated as `number | string`.  Without user-brancher
# recognition, `x + 1` in the true branch would warn; with it, `x`
# is narrowed to `number` → no warning.
my-if(c, t, f): if(c, t, f)

` { type: "(number | string) → number" }
safe-add(x): my-if(x number?, x + 1, 0)

result: safe-add(42)
